name: Windmill Hill City Farm Orchard
description: A well-established city farm with public fruit trees including apples and plums.

name: Severn Beach Sea Beet
short_description: Coastal greens along the Severn Estuary.
description: Find Sea Beet and Orache along the shingle banks of the estuary path.

name: Ashton Court Deer Park Chestnuts
description: Large sweet chestnut trees located near the lower mansion car park area.

name: Incredible Edible Totterdown
short_description: Community planters with herbs and veg.
description: Street-side planters maintained by locals offering free herbs and seasonal vegetables.

name: Leigh Woods Wild Garlic
description: A famous spot for wild garlic in the spring. Found throughout the woodland floors.

name: Bristol-Bath Railway Path Berries
short_description: Forage blackberries along the cycle path.
description: Miles of blackberry brambles line this popular cycling and walking route.

name: Horfield Community Orchard
description: Over 100 varieties of apples, pears, and soft fruits managed by the community.

name: Bristol Harbourside Fennel
short_description: Wild bronze fennel in industrial areas.
description: Stands of wild fennel are often found growing in the cracks of the old dockside stones.

name: Blaise Castle Hazelnuts
description: Hazel trees are abundant in the limestone woods around the castle estate.

name: St Werburghs City Farm Orchard
short_description: Apples and berries at the city farm.
description: Free-to-access perimeter trees including damsons and cooking apples.

name: Portishead Marina Samphire
description: Found on the salt marshes nearby. Ensure you check tide times before foraging.

name: Purdown Sloes
short_description: Blackthorn bushes near the BT Tower.
description: Large crops of sloes can be found in the hedgerows across the Purdown open space.

name: Incredible Edible Bristol Temple Meads
description: Planters near the station entrance feature edible flowers and hardy herbs.

name: Arnos Vale Walnuts
description: Old walnut trees can be found within the wilder wooded areas of the cemetery estate.

name: Stockwood Open Space Elder
short_description: High yield of elderflower and berries.
description: A great spot for elderflower in June and deep purple elderberries in September.
